    "long_instructions": "::: details [**1. Identify the Missing Pieces**]\r\nBefore running the code, **review the print statements**. What variables are being used that have not been defined?\r\n* Think about **what kind of values** each variable should store.\r\n* If you're unsure, ask the AI Tutor: *\"What types of values should each variable have?\"*\r\n:::\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n::: details [**2: Define the Variables**]\r\nNow, **declare and assign values** to each missing variable in the program.\r\n* If you get stuck, ask the AI Tutor, *\"How do I declare a variable in Python?\"*\r\n:::\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n::: details [**3. Fix the Print Statements**]\r\nLook at the print statements. Are all the variables inside them correctly formatted?\r\n\r\nIf your program gives an error when printing numbers, **what needs to change**?\r\n* Hint: You may need to **convert non-string variables** before printing!\r\n:::\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n::: details [**4. Predict the Output**]\r\nBefore running your code, **take a moment to think**:\r\n* What do you expect the program to print?\r\n* Will the output **make sense** based on how you formatted the print statements?\r\n\r\nIf you're unsure, ask the AI Tutor: *\"Can you help me predict what the output should look like?\"*\r\n:::\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n::: details [**5. Run and Debug**]\r\nRun your program and check if the output matches your expectations.\r\n\r\nIf something looks wrong, ask the AI Tutor: *\"Why is my output different from what I expected?\"*\r\n\r\nRemember, debugging is part of the process! Instead of giving direct answers, the AI Tutor will **guide you with hints and explanations** to help you improve your understanding.\r\n:::"
